# UI + Docker refresh (Stellar-Shark)

When a task modifies anything under `web/` that ships in the Vite build (`src/`, `index.html`, `tailwind.config.js`, etc.), finish by refreshing what users see in Docker:

1. From the **repository root**, run: `npm run docker:ui`

That script runs `npm run build` (Vite), rebuilds the `app` image (which bakes `web/dist` via the Dockerfile), and recreates the `app` container with `docker compose up -d app`.

If Docker is not used and the user runs `npm run dev` / Electron only, a local `npm run build` may still be useful to verify the production bundle; follow the user’s setup when they are not on Docker.
